    "questions": [
        {
            "id": "3009837a627340b186cae",
            "questionText": "A hospital prepares a sample of Technetium-99m ($!$\\text{Tc-99m}$!$) with an initial activity ($!$A_0$!$) of $!$10 \\text{ mCi}$!$ at 8:00 AM. Technetium-99m is used for medical imaging, and it has a half-life ($!$T_{1/2}$!$) of approximately 6 hours due to its gamma decay properties. Considering the need to efficiently schedule imaging procedures and the spontaneous decay of the sample, calculate the activity ($!$A$!$) of the Technetium-99m sample at 8:00 PM on the same day. Remember to first calculate the decay constant ($!$\\lambda$!$) using the given half-life, and then use the activity decay formula to determine the remaining activity after the specified time period.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "9e7bc18503e14381ad4a1",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the correct formula to compute the decay constant ($!$\\lambda$!$) from the half-life ($!$T_{1/2}$!$). Please choose the proper formula from the options below.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "ee32cb2b-386d-44a5-967d-83065fc7128a",
                        "4a96e678-9acd-4cc8-8563-b2cf4e679b6d"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\lambda = \\frac{\\ln 2}{T_{1/2}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\lambda = \\frac{T_{1/2}}{\\ln 2}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\lambda = \\frac{0.5}{T_{1/2}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "94c15bce014144f1867fa",
                    "stepText": "Great, now use the formula you selected along with the given half-life of $!$6\\text{ hours}$!$ to compute the decay constant ($!$\\lambda$!$). Please calculate and enter the numerical value.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "0.1155"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "hr^{-1}",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "ee32cb2b-386d-44a5-967d-83065fc7128a",
                        "4a96e678-9acd-4cc8-8563-b2cf4e679b6d"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "688ffb928a20436da958e",
                    "stepText": "Now, determine the elapsed time ($!$\\Delta t$!$) from 8:00 AM to 8:00 PM. Please calculate the time difference in hours.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "12"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "hours",
                    "stepConcepts": [],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "b9bf3dd9f19a449e84daf",
                    "stepText": "Excellent! Now, choose the correct decay formula for calculating the activity ($!$A$!$) given the initial activity ($!$A_0$!$) and the decay constant ($!$\\lambda$!$). Which of the following formulas is appropriate?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "25c877b8-9a98-41c4-9844-addf85fe40a5",
                        "4a96e678-9acd-4cc8-8563-b2cf4e679b6d"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$A = A_0 \\cdot e^{-\\lambda \\Delta t}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$A = A_0 \\cdot \\lambda \\Delta t$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$A = A_0 \\cdot e^{\\lambda \\Delta t}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "1e973f73fb424001943f9",
                    "stepText": "Finally, using the decay formula and the calculated values ($!$A_0 = 10\\text{ mCi}$!$, $!$\\lambda = 0.1155\\text{ hr}^{-1}$!$, and $!$\\Delta t = 12\\text{ hours}$!$), compute the remaining activity at 8:00 PM. Please provide the numerical value.",
