                    "options": []
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "46d2c7de4c174752bc22c",
            "questionText": "An archaeologist discovers an ancient wooden artifact. Analysis shows that the current activity of Carbon-14 ($!$^{14}\\text{C}$!$) in the artifact is 30% of the activity found in living wood today. Given that Carbon-14 decays with a half-life ($!$T_{1/2}$!$) of 5,730 years, determine the approximate age of the wooden artifact.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "f864de4952c944cfa6863",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the correct formula that describes radioactive decay using the half-life concept. Please select the formula which represents the decay of activity over time.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "ee32cb2b-386d-44a5-967d-83065fc7128a",
                        "25c877b8-9a98-41c4-9844-addf85fe40a5"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$A=A_0\\left(\\frac{1}{2}\\right)^{\\frac{t}{T_{1/2}}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$A=A_0\\left(2\\right)^{\\frac{t}{T_{1/2}}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$A=A_0\\left(1-\\frac{t}{T_{1/2}}\\right)$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$A=A_0e^{-\\frac{t}{T_{1/2}}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "e404d3e7bb51482b82c2e",
                    "stepText": "Great! Now that you have the correct decay formula, substitute the given information. Knowing that the current activity is 30% of the original activity and that $!$T_{1/2}=5730$!$ years, write the equation that relates these values. Choose the option that correctly expresses the relation using a logarithmic form.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "ee32cb2b-386d-44a5-967d-83065fc7128a"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\ln(0.30)=\\frac{t}{5730}\\ln(\\frac{1}{2})$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\ln(0.30)=\\frac{5730}{t}\\ln(\\frac{1}{2})$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\ln(0.30)=t\\ln(\\frac{1}{2})$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\ln(0.30)=\\frac{t}{5730}\\ln(2)$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "7257b288a34f4c0897425",
                    "stepText": "Now, using the relation from the previous step, solve for $!$t$!$. Calculate the product after isolating $!$t$!$ and determine its numerical value. Enter the numerical result along with the proper time unit.",
